@startuml
title Logging Service JPA Entities Overview

hide empty members
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false

top to bottom direction
scale 800 width

package "Reference Data" {
  class PdpoIdentifierEntity <<Entity>>
}

package "PDPO Logging Domain" {
  class PdpoLogEntity <<Entity>>
  class PdpoLogIndividualEntity <<Entity>>
  enum PdpoCategory <<Enum>>
}

PdpoIdentifierEntity -[hidden]down-> PdpoLogEntity
PdpoLogEntity -[hidden]down-> PdpoLogIndividualEntity

PdpoIdentifierEntity ||--o{ PdpoLogEntity
PdpoLogEntity ||--o{ PdpoLogIndividualEntity
PdpoCategory <.. PdpoLogEntity

note bottom of PdpoIdentifierEntity
Stores the business identifier
used to group related PDPO logs.
end note

note left of PdpoLogEntity
Central audit record for a PDPO event.

Optional recipient fields are only
populated for DISCLOSURE events.
end note

note right of PdpoLogIndividualEntity
One log entry can reference
multiple impacted individuals.
end note

note bottom of PdpoCategory
Values:
- COLLECTION
- ALTERATION
- CONSULTATION
- DISCLOSURE
- COMBINATION
- ERASURE
end note

@enduml
